<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="335" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,654,1723]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,762,787]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a noun in apposition taken from the fictional language Sindarin created by J.R.R. Tolkien. The Sindarin is one of the languages spoken by the Elves. The word “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1167,1241,798,823]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Thiodina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perian">perian</taxonomicName>
” is translated as “small” and was used to refer to the Hobbits, the smaller kind of Middle Earth; in reference to its small size, to date the smallest thiodinine ever discovered (see description).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="335" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,654,1723]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,906,931]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The males resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[673,945,906,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Thiodina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="nicoleti" status="comb. nov." variety="minuta">
<emphasis box="[673,803,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Th. nicoleti</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[820,945,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Th. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[954,1086,906,931]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[954,1086,906,931]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1146,1252,906,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Thiodina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firme" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1146,1252,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Th. firme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1261,1354,906,931]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1261,1354,906,931]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the general appearance of body, but differ in the length of the embolus of the palp, longer in this species (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1424,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 26. Thiodina perian sp. nov. A male palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view; C same, dorsal view; D same, prolateral; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, dorsal view (cleared)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098092/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Fig. 26A</figureCitation>
). The females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[501,623,978,1003]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cyllodania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[501,623,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Th. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[629,758,978,1003]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[629,758,978,1003]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the shape of spermathecae, but differ by the longer ducts (
<figureCitation box="[159,259,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 26. Thiodina perian sp. nov. A male palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view; C same, dorsal view; D same, prolateral; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, dorsal view (cleared)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098092/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Fig. 26F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="335" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,654,1723]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,419,1050,1075]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Total length: 1.61. Carapace 0.84 long, 0.54 wide, 0.35 high. Ocular quadrangle 0.46 long. Anterior and posterior eye row 0.54 wide. Chelicera paturon with two promarginal teeth, the distal one bicuspid, and one retromarginal bicuspid tooth. Excavation of chelicera absent. Length of femur: I 0.42, II 0.35, III 0.34, IV 0.43; patella + tibia: I 0.53, II 0.41, III 0.38, IV 0.52; metatarsus + tarsus: I 0.43, II 0.37, III 0.40, IV 0.48. Leg formula: 4123. Leg spination: femur I‒III d0-1-1, p0, r0; IV d1-1-1, p0, r0; patella I‒IV 0; tibia I p0, r0, 
<date box="[1326,1356,1195,1219]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">v2</date>
*-0-2a- 1p; II p0, r0, 
<date box="[298,323,1231,1255]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">v1</date>
r-0-0; III 0; IV p0, r0, v0; metatarsus I‒II 
<date box="[791,846,1231,1255]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">v2-2</date>
; III p0, r1di, v0; IV p0, r0 (r1di right), v0. Palp (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 26. Thiodina perian sp. nov. A male palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view; C same, dorsal view; D same, prolateral; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, dorsal view (cleared)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098092/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Figs 26A‒26D</figureCitation>
): tibia wider than long, RTA thin and hook-shaped, RvTA squared (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1227,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 26. Thiodina perian sp. nov. A male palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view; C same, dorsal view; D same, prolateral; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, dorsal view (cleared)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098092/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Figs 26B‒26C</figureCitation>
); embolus simple, fixed to the tegulum, arising prolaterally, with a path of 450° (1T+90°) before the distal coil (
<figureCitation box="[1184,1355,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 26. Thiodina perian sp. nov. A male palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view; C same, dorsal view; D same, prolateral; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, dorsal view (cleared)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098092/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Figs 26A‒26B</figureCitation>
). Color in alcohol: carapace yellow with black borders, eyes area black, two brown stripes on thoracic region, abdomen dorsally as in genus, ventrally white with dark areas. Femur I yellow, patella I distally dark, tibia and metatarsus I black, tarsus yellow; the rest of the legs as the leg I, but the black areas are light brown (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1310,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1777,1799]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[151,1436,373,1756]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 25. Thiodinaperian sp. nov. A male holotype, dorsal; B same, lateral; C same, ventral; D female paratype, dorsal; E same, lateral; F same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098090/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Figs 25A‒25C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,654,1723]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1446,1471]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Female.</emphasis>
Total length: 1.75. Carapace 0.84 long, 0.54 wide, 0.35 high. Ocular quadrangle 0.48 long. Anterior eye row 0.56 wide and posterior 0.58 wide. Chelicera paturon with the same dentition as the male. Length of femur: I 0.38, II 0.32, III 0.32, IV 0.46; patella + tibia: I 0.49, II 0.38, III 0.37, IV 0.54; metatarsus + tarsus: I 0.41, II 0.35, III 0.41, IV 0.49. Leg formula: 4 132. Leg spination: femur I‒III d0-1-1, p0, r0; IV d1-1-1, p0, r0; patella I‒ IV 0; tibia I p0, r0, 
<date box="[373,426,1591,1615]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">v2-2</date>
a-2; II p0, r0, 
<date box="[582,608,1591,1615]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">v1</date>
r-1r-0; III‒IV 0; metatarsus I‒II 
<date box="[975,1029,1591,1615]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">v2-2</date>
; III‒IV 0. Epigyne (
<figureCitation box="[1259,1425,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,831,1942]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 26. Thiodina perian sp. nov. A male palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view; C same, dorsal view; D same, prolateral; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, dorsal view (cleared)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098092/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Figs 26E‒26F</figureCitation>
): posterior edge simple, without lobes, copulatory openings posteriorly placed. Color in alcohol: carapace and abdomen as in male. Legs yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
